The Police Command in Osun on Tuesday said it had rescued Mr Yinka Okunade, who was kidnapped along Osu-Ife Expressway on April 24. Police spokesperson in Osun, SP Yemisi Opalola, told newsmen that Okunade was released at 10 p.m. on Monday, after an intense pressure on the kidnappers by the police. “This is to inform members of the public that due to intensive pressure on the kidnappers by the police, Okunade, who was kidnapped on April 24, has been released. “The victim was released yesterday night unhurt and has reunited with his family,” she said The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that gunmen waylaid a commercial bus travelling along Osu-Ife-Ilesha expressway last Saturday and abducted Okunade. (NAN) Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related Gunmen kidnap 3 travellers in OsunThe Police Command in Osun has confirmed the alleged kidnapping of three travellers along Ilesha-Akure Express in Osun on Monday night.February 10, 2021In "General News"Police confirms release of woman kidnapped with Ekiti CommissionerPolice Command in Ekiti confirm release of woman kidnapped on April 26, along with state Commissioner for Agriculture, Mr Olabode Folorunsho.May 1, 2020In "Defence/Security"Assault: Woman writes IGP, demands N200m compensationMrs Adetola Abdulazeez, the woman assaulted by two police officers enforcing the lockdown directive in Osun,is demanding 200 compensation from IGP.April 27, 2020In "General News" Gunmen kidnap 3 travellers in OsunThe Police Command in Osun has confirmed the alleged kidnapping of three travellers along Ilesha-Akure Express in Osun on Monday night.February 10, 2021In "General News"Police confirms rele